text: Eoacmaea albonotata is a species of sea snail, a true limpet, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eoacmaeidae, one of the families of true limpets. The species is found off Natal, South Africa. ==References== * Smith, E.A. (1901) On South African marine shells, with descriptions of new species. Journal of Conchology, 10, 104–116, 1 pl. * Nakano T. & Ozawa T. (2007). Worldwide phylogeography of limpets of the order Patellogastropoda: molecular, morphological and paleontological evidence. Journal of Molluscan Studies 73(1): 79–99 Category:Eoacmaeidae Category:Gastropods described in 1901
title: Eoacmaea albonotata
